BCM is clamping down on illegal car washing along the beachfront. Metro spokesman Samkelo Ngwenya said those caught using the car washers’ services could face six months in jail or a R10 000 fine. “On Saturday May 19, BCM law enforcement services shut down unlawful washing of vehicles in Buffalo City at the beachfront. Vehicle owners whose cars were washed were prosecuted,” said Ngwenya. For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.